## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-314">在修改其<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate%2A> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> 对象之前,应用程序必须使用暂停正在<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>运行的实例。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-314">Applications must use <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate%2A> to pause a running instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> before modifying its <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-315">例如, 当暂停时<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> , 可以加载、卸载、启用和禁用<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>对象。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-315">For example, while the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> is paused, you can load, unload, enable, and disable <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-316">当<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer>已准备好接受修改时, 将引发此事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-316">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> raises this event when it is ready to accept modifications.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-317">为<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件创建委托时, 需要标识将处理该事件的方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-317">When you create a delegate for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event, you identify the method that will handle the event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-318">若要将事件与事件处理程序关联，请将该委托的一个实例添加到事件中。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-318">To associate the event with your event handler, add an instance of the delegate to the event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-319">除非移除了该委托，否则每当发生该事件时就会调用事件处理程序。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-319">The event handler is called whenever the event occurs, unless you remove the delegate.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-320">有关事件处理程序委托的详细信息, 请参阅[事件和委托](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=162418)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-320">For more information about event-handler delegates, see [Events and Delegates](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=162418).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-321">下面的示例演示了一个加载和卸载<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>对象的控制台应用程序。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-321">The following example shows a console application that loads and unloads <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-322">应用程序使用<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate%2A>方法请求语音识别引擎暂停, 使其可以接收更新。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-322">The application uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate%2A> method to request the speech recognition engine to pause so it can receive an update.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-323">然后, 应用程序将加载或<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>卸载对象。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-323">The application then loads or unloads a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-324">在每次更新时, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件处理程序会将当前加载<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>的对象的名称和状态写入控制台。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-324">At each update, a handler for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event writes the name and status of the currently loaded <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objects to the console.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-325">加载和卸载语法时, 应用程序首先识别场动物的名称, 然后识别场动物的名称和水果的名称, 然后仅识别水果的名称。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-325">As grammars are loaded and unloaded, the application first recognizes the names of farm animals, then the names of farm animals and the names of fruits, then only the names of fruits.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Collections.Generic;  
using System.Threading;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    private static SpeechRecognizer recognizer;  
    public static void Main(string[] args)  
    {  
  
      // Initialize a shared speech recognition engine.  
      recognizer = new SpeechRecognizer();  
  
      // Create the first grammar - Farm.  
      Choices animals = new Choices(new string[] { "cow", "pig", "goat" });  
      GrammarBuilder farm = new GrammarBuilder(animals);  
      Grammar farmAnimals = new Grammar(farm);  
      farmAnimals.Name = "Farm";  
  
      // Create the second grammar - Fruit.  
      Choices fruit = new Choices(new string[] { "apples", "peaches", "oranges" });  
      GrammarBuilder favorite = new GrammarBuilder(fruit);  
      Grammar favoriteFruit = new Grammar(favorite);  
      favoriteFruit.Name = "Fruit";  
  
      // Attach event handlers.  
      recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=  
        new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
      recognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached +=  
        new EventHandler<RecognizerUpdateReachedEventArgs>(recognizer_RecognizerUpdateReached);  
      recognizer.StateChanged +=   
        new EventHandler<StateChangedEventArgs>(recognizer_StateChanged);  
  
      // Load the Farm grammar.  
      recognizer.LoadGrammar(farmAnimals);  
      Console.WriteLine("Grammar Farm is loaded");  
  
      // Pause to recognize farm animals.  
      Thread.Sleep(7000);  
      Console.WriteLine();  
  
      // Request an update and load the Fruit grammar.  
      recognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate();  
      recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(favoriteFruit);  
      Thread.Sleep(5000);  
  
      // Request an update and unload the Farm grammar.  
      recognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate();  
      recognizer.UnloadGrammar(farmAnimals);  
      Thread.Sleep(5000);  
  
      // Keep the console window open.  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Press any key to exit...");  
      Console.ReadKey();  
    }  
  
    // Put the shared speech recognizer into "listening" mode.  
    static void recognizer_StateChanged(object sender, StateChangedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      if (e.RecognizerState != RecognizerState.Stopped)  
      {  
        recognizer.EmulateRecognizeAsync("Start listening");  
      }  
    }  
  
    // At the update, get the names and enabled status of the currently loaded grammars.  
    public static void recognizer_RecognizerUpdateReached(  
      object sender, RecognizerUpdateReachedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Update reached:");  
      Thread.Sleep(1000);  
  
      string qualifier;  
      List<Grammar> grammars = new List<Grammar>(recognizer.Grammars);  
      foreach (Grammar g in grammars)  
      {  
        qualifier = (g.Enabled) ? "enabled" : "disabled";  
        Console.WriteLine("  Grammar {0} is loaded and is {1}.",  
        g.Name, qualifier);  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Write the text of the recognized phrase to the console.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("  Speech recognized: " + e.Result.Text);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-327">使用此方法将更改同步到共享识别器。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-327">Use this method to synchronize changes to the shared recognizer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-328">例如, 如果在识别器正在处理输入时加载或卸载语音识别语法, 请使用此方法和<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件, 将应用程序行为与识别器的状态进行同步。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-328">For example, if you load or unload a speech recognition grammar while the recognizer is processing input, use this method and the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event to synchronize your application behavior with the state of the recognizer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-329">调用此方法时, 识别器将暂停或完成异步操作并生成一个<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-329">When this method is called, the recognizer pauses or completes asynchronous operations and generates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-330">然后<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> , 事件处理程序可以在识别操作之间修改识别器的状态。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-330">A <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event handler can then modify the state of the recognizer in between recognition operations.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-331">调用此方法时:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-331">When this method is called:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-332">如果识别器未处理输入, 则识别器会立即生成<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-332">If the recognizer is not processing input, the recognizer immediately generates the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-333">如果识别器正在处理由无声或背景噪音组成的输入, 识别器将暂停识别操作并生成<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-333">If the recognizer is processing input that consists of silence or background noise, the recognizer pauses the recognition operation and generates the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-334">如果识别器正在处理的输入不包括无声或背景干扰, 则识别器完成识别操作, 然后生成<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-334">If the recognizer is processing input that does not consist of silence or background noise, the recognizer completes the recognition operation and then generates the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-335">识别器处理<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件时:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-335">While the recognizer is handling the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-336">识别器不处理输入, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A>属性的值保持不变。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-336">The recognizer does not process input, and the value of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A> property remains the same.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-337">识别器继续收集输入, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioPosition%2A>属性的值可以更改。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-337">The recognizer continues to collect input, and the value of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioPosition%2A> property can change.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-338">若要更改共享识别器在应用程序处理<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechRecognized>事件时是否暂停识别操作, 请<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.PauseRecognizerOnRecognition%2A>使用属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-338">To change whether the shared recognizer pauses recognition operations while an application is handling a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechRecognized> event, use the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.PauseRecognizerOnRecognition%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-339">下面的示例演示了一个加载和卸载<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>对象的控制台应用程序。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-339">The following example shows a console application that loads and unloads <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-340">应用程序使用<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate%2A>方法请求语音识别引擎暂停, 使其可以接收更新。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-340">The application uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate%2A> method to request the speech recognition engine to pause so it can receive an update.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-341">然后, 应用程序将加载或<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>卸载对象。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-341">The application then loads or unloads a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-342">在每次更新时, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached>事件处理程序会将当前加载<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>的对象的名称和状态写入控制台。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-342">At each update, a handler for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached> event writes the name and status of the currently loaded <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objects to the console.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0fd7-343">加载和卸载语法时, 应用程序首先识别场动物的名称, 然后识别场动物的名称和水果的名称, 然后仅识别水果的名称。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0fd7-343">As grammars are loaded and unloaded, the application first recognizes the names of farm animals, then the names of farm animals and the names of fruits, then only the names of fruits.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Collections.Generic;  
using System.Threading;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    private static SpeechRecognizer recognizer;  
    public static void Main(string[] args)  
    {  
  
      // Initialize an in-process speech recognition engine and configure its input.  
      recognizer = new SpeechRecognizer();  
  
      // Create the first grammar - Farm.  
      Choices animals = new Choices(new string[] { "cow", "pig", "goat" });  
      GrammarBuilder farm = new GrammarBuilder(animals);  
      Grammar farmAnimals = new Grammar(farm);  
      farmAnimals.Name = "Farm";  
  
      // Create the second grammar - Fruit.  
      Choices fruit = new Choices(new string[] { "apples", "peaches", "oranges" });  
      GrammarBuilder favorite = new GrammarBuilder(fruit);  
      Grammar favoriteFruit = new Grammar(favorite);  
      favoriteFruit.Name = "Fruit";  
  
      // Attach event handlers.  
      recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=  
        new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
      recognizer.RecognizerUpdateReached +=  
        new EventHandler<RecognizerUpdateReachedEventArgs>(recognizer_RecognizerUpdateReached);  
  
      // Check to see if recognizer is loaded, wait if it is not loaded.  
      if (recognizer.State != RecognizerState.Listening)  
      {  
        Thread.Sleep(5000);  
  
        // Put recognizer in listening state.  
        recognizer.EmulateRecognizeAsync("Start listening");  
      }  
  
      // Load the Farm grammar.  
      recognizer.LoadGrammar(farmAnimals);  
      Console.WriteLine("Grammar Farm is loaded");  
  
      // Pause to recognize farm animals.  
      Thread.Sleep(7000);  
      Console.WriteLine();  
  
      // Request an update and load the Fruit grammar.  
      recognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate();  
      recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(favoriteFruit);  
      Thread.Sleep(5000);  
  
      // Request an update and unload the Farm grammar.  
      recognizer.RequestRecognizerUpdate();  
      recognizer.UnloadGrammar(farmAnimals);  
      Thread.Sleep(5000);  
  
      // Keep the console window open.  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Press any key to exit...");  
      Console.ReadKey();  
    }  
  
    public static void recognizer_RecognizerUpdateReached(object sender, RecognizerUpdateReachedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      // At the update, get the names and enabled status of the currently loaded grammars.  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Update reached:");  
      Thread.Sleep(1000);  
      string qualifier;  
      List<Grammar> grammars = new List<Grammar>(recognizer.Grammars);  
      foreach (Grammar g in grammars)  
      {  
        qualifier = (g.Enabled) ? "enabled" : "disabled";  
        Console.WriteLine("  Grammar {0} is loaded and is {1}.",  
        g.Name, qualifier);  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Write the text of the recognized phrase to the console.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("  Speech recognized: " + e.Result.Text);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
